g.text: The Safety Seal Certification is a voluntary certification scheme that affirms that an establishment is compliant with the minimum public health standards set by the government and uses or integrates its contact tracing with StaySafe.ph. The DILG issues the Safety Seal for: - Provincial Capitols, City/Municipal Halls - All other LGUs facilities and buildings - Police camps and stations - BFP Offices and Fire Stations - Barangay Halls and Facilities - All other public establishments not covered by other
